The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Bomb scare in flight
                                                                                                           Bomb scare in flight 
										      Mumbai, July 23 (PTI): A passenger on board an Indigo flight from Delhi was arrested after he claimed there was a bomb in the aircraft and the plane should be diverted to Pakistan, an airport spokesperson said.   A passenger named Sanjay Mallik on Indigo flight 6E181 from Delhi arrested by CISF on landing at 11: 45 hours. A spokesperson for the Mumbai International Airport Limited (MIAL) told that about 15 minutes before landing in Mumbai, that person claimed there was a bomb in the aircraft and the flight should be diverted to Pakistan,  The 28-year-old Malik, who hails from Haryana, boarded the flight at Delhi and when he was served apple juice while flying, he said that there was a bomb in the juice packet.   This triggered a panic in the flight. Soon after the flight landed here, The person was handed over to security personnel at the airport,  Police said, He was flying alone in the flight, and his questioning was going on.
                                                                                                                                       
